{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-detail-js","path":"/post/how-to-install-magento-2-in-windows-xampp/","result":{"data":{"wpPost":{"title":"How to Install Magento 2 in Windows XAMPP","content":"\n<p>Magento 2 is a widely popular e-commerce platform, known for its scalability, flexibility, and customization options. It caters to the needs of both small and large businesses, offering an intuitive interface and a robust toolkit for creating professional online stores.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By installing Magento 2 on XAMPP, you can create a local development environment for experimentation with various features, customization of themes and extensions, and testing store performance, all without any impact on your live website. The guide provides detailed and easy-to-follow instructions for installing Magento 2 on Windows XAMPP, enabling you to swiftly create your desired online store in no time. Now letâ€™s start with the process of <strong><em>how to install Magento 2 in windows XAMPP.</em></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to Install Magento 2 in Windows XAMPP: A Step-by-Step Guide</h1>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step: 1</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.apachefriends.org/download.html\">Download and install XAMPP</a> on your Windows computer. This software bundle includes Apache, MySQL, and PHP, which are all necessary for running Magento 2.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"624\" height=\"354\" src=\"/8ff3e5fc-9d12-4e7c-86bf-1a6e4e8a8bf5\"></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step: 2</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Download the latest version of <a href=\"https://github.com/magento/magento2\">Magento 2</a> from the official website.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step: 3</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Extract the Magento 2 files to the &#8220;htdocs&#8221; folder located in the XAMPP installation directory.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"623\" height=\"250\" src=\"/2f3411fd-c9b3-42ea-8f1e-a7b0db9953d6\"></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step: 4</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Start the Apache and MySQL modules in the XAMPP control panel.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"513\" height=\"309\" src=\"/f21a5297-a99d-4d43-a40d-0e396546d19b\"></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step: 5</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">Open your web browser and navigate to &#8220;http://localhost/phpmyadmin&#8221; to create a new database for Magento 2.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"624\" height=\"241\" src=\"/94301d64-9525-426f-b92b-f92e619db307\"><br></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\"></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step: 6</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">In your web browser, navigate to &#8220;http://localhost/[folder name]&#8221; (where &#8220;folder name&#8221; is the name of the folder where you extracted the Magento 2 files in step 3). This will start the Magento 2 installation process.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step:7</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Follow the prompts to complete the installation, including providing the necessary information for your new database (created in step 5).</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step: 8</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Once the installation is complete, you can access the Magento 2 admin panel by navigating to &#8220;http://localhost/[folder name]/admin&#8221; in your web browser.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">That&#8217;s it! You have now successfully installed Magento 2 on your Windows computer using XAMPP.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">If you need to move your <a href=\"/how-to-move-magento-2-from-localhost-to-server/\">Magento 2 website from localhost to a server</a>, check out our guide on how to move Magento 2 from localhost to server.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conclusion</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This article provides a comprehensive guide on <strong><em>how to install Magento 2 in Windows XAMPP</em></strong>, covering all the necessary steps and configurations required for a successful setup. If you are looking to get started with <strong><em><a href=\"/how-to-setup-magento-2/\">Magento 2 setup</a> in XAMPP</em></strong>, this guide will walk you through the entire process, from downloading and installing XAMPP to configuring your environment and installing Magento 2. By following these steps, you can easily set up a local development environment and start building your Magento store on Windows XAMPP.</p>\n<div class='sfsi_Sicons sfsi_Sicons_position_left' style='float: none; vertical-align: middle; text-align:left'><div style='margin:0px 8px 0px 0px; line-height: 24px'><span>Please follow and like us:</span></div><div class='sfsi_socialwpr'><div class='sf_fb_share sf_icon' style='text-align:left;vertical-align: middle;'><a  target='_blank' rel='noopener' href='https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=/how-to-install-magento-2-in-windows-xampp/' style='display:inline-block;'><img class='sfsi_wicon'  data-pin-nopin='true' alt='fb-share-icon' title='Facebook Share' src='https://webguru.dev/wp-content/plugins/ultimate-social-media-icons/images/share_icons/fb_icons/en_US.svg' /></a></div><div class='sf_twiter sf_icon' style='display: inline-block;vertical-align: middle;width: auto;margin-left: 7px;'>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a target='_blank' rel='noopener' href='https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=How+to+Install+Magento+2+in+Windows+XAMPP+https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fhow-to-install-magento-2-in-windows-xampp%2F'style='display:inline-block' >\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img data-pin-nopin= true class='sfsi_wicon' src='https://webguru.dev/wp-content/plugins/ultimate-